==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flamen
<hw>Fla"men</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> E.
<plw>Flammens</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, L. <plw>Flamines</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.]</ety> <fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A
priest devoted to the service of a particular god, from whom he received
a distinguishing epithet. The most honored were those of Jupiter, Mars,
and Quirinus, called respectively <stype>Flamen Dialis</stype>,
<stype>Flamen Martialis</stype>, and <stype>Flamen
Quirinalis</stype>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Affrights the <qex>flamens</qex> at their service quaint.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>flamenco</ent>⟦br⟧
